Reasoning: The paper proposes an information-theoretic model for evaluating the intelligence level of AI systems, which involves the concept of entropy and capacity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on a case study of AlphaZero, which is an AI system that uses reinforcement learning and self-play, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the learning process of AlphaZero, which involves iterative decoding, suggesting that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category, as it proposes a bound for intelligent agents in the form of Shannon's capacity.
